Global Computer Aided Manufacturing Market (2025-2032)
Market Highlights:

Projected CAGR: 7.98% from 2021-2028.
Estimated market value: USD 5.066 billion by 2028.
Key growth drivers: Automation adoption, IoT integration, rapid industrialization, and R&D investments.
Major restraints: Availability of free/open-source software, high operational costs, and lack of skilled personnel.
Definition and Overview:

CAM refers to software that automates manufacturing processes, minimizing human errors and enhancing productivity.
